caption: I've come here for dinner several times and it's excellent. It's asian fusion and I've never left disappointed. This trip I stopped by in the morning to go to their cafe and was pleasantly surprised by it as well. I was meeting a coworker and stayed for a while. Plenty of space to spread out, all the orders were put in by an app and the staff brought them very quickly. I had a flat white that was very good, and ended up getting a drip coffee after I finished. The drip was more of a light roast and, while I normally prefer dark, I enjoyed it as well. You can tell they use good quality, fresh roasted beans.
Horrible service , especially from the lady that works as hostess. Her attitude, arrogance and lack of sense of service represent very well the decay of a once great DC restaurant.

really enjoyed my experience at Maketto. I have been wanting to go for quite some time. And I think they did a really nice fusion of Asian flavors with some modern ingredients. I will say everything tasted greatly but it wasn’t my favorite things I have eaten. The fried chicken was great but did have an overpowering flavor of fish sauce. The shrimp dumplings were amazing and the sauce was very similar to papaya salad, but I am not the biggest fan of ground shrimp. I think the beef rice was amazing out of everything.
it’s super bomb!!
One of the best Asian food in DC
The Pork buns rock!
I can see why some people like it, but meh.
I saw roaches. But the food was good
The service was absolutely great. Food was pretty good as well.
Excellent food, can't wait till Covid restrictions allow me to enjoy a place like Maketto normally. We do take out and it is a one of our go to spots because.....it is simply delicious

Mr.Bruner -Yang had me with the delicious  ramen at Toki Underground. Maketto is an entirely  different , wonderful,  and new experience. When you  walk in the vibe is modern zen. Clean lines, lots of light, and delicious  aromas.We were lucky  and got the top floor to ourselves. The contactless  ordering  and diligent  staff make the experience worry free. The food was DELICIOUS!!!! That sauce for those  soft pillowy pork baos needs to be bottled and sold. The scallion  pancakes were crispy,  oniony, savory bliss! The chicken wings we the absolute definition  of umami and the spice sneaks up on you in the best way! If you are a fan of drunken noodles  try the drunken shrimp fried rice , it was so light and fluffy with plump juicy shrimp ! It had just the right balance of flavors especially  with the sauce on the side! The fried chicken with five spice caramel had a crispyness that all chicken should aspire too! We will be back again and again ! Also, applause  for the staff and culinary geniuses  who carry out daily  service, Bravo!

Went here for Valentine's day because my girlfriend loves Asian food and it was exactly what we needed the cocktails were awesome and the vibe even better. Exceptional service and would highly recommend for any occasion even if Maketto is the occasion. I described the infusion of cloths and fashion as like the coffee house and art thing but better.

Besides being out of chicken, the food was next level. The service was outstanding, truly white linen yet personal and inviting. If not for the 90's vibe and casual dress I would have mistaken it for a Michelin 3-4 star.

Food is delicious! If you like Bao, then their pork boa is a must. Perfectly fried vegetable spring rolls, and a great selection of drinks and cocktails. Minus one star because the app they are using for orders (sot down meal) automatically adds a 20% gratuity. I prefer to be able to tip in cash.
Great food and service. Outdoor heated covid-safe patio!  Recommend the scallion pancakes, shrimp dumplings, and bok choy dishes in particular, but didn't eat anything bad. Great service too. A+!
Always incredible, the Fried Chicken, cauliflower, and Gruyere dumplings are OUT OF THIS WORLD!!
Atlas District is a great up and coming neighborhood. The numerous interesting small and medium plates at Maketto makes it perfect for a quick bite as part of a bigger evening.
Chicken lo mein was excellent and vegetable bao but vegetable dumplings weren't very good but could be because takeaway as opposed to having had them there in the past
A very interesting retail, coffee shop, bar, restaurant combo.  The food is incredible. Try the eggplant dish. The chicken was awesome as well.

The staff is extremely warm and welcoming!  The food is DELICIOUS!  I had drunken shrimp fried rice, snow pea tips and scallion pancakes!  They are among my favorites!  The pastries and cookies are delightful as well!

I'm usually skeptical of high-end pan-Asian/Asian fusion, and I'm extra skeptical when a restaurant doubles as a streetwear shop, but I happily stuffed my words into their bao and gobbled them down.  I came here with my mom for a weekend brunch. They have plentiful outdoor seating options, and a great online ordering system (GoTab.io). We ordered espresso drinks, scallion pancakes, and the red pork bao platter. The coffees were decent, though my bar is high coming from Seattle, definitely as good as I'd expect on the East Coast. The pancakes had a wonderful crisp outer layer, and plenty of chewy goodness inside. They were a bit fatter than what I'm used to, but delicious in their own way. The bao platter was a standout winner. The pork was succulent, the bao were fresh and fluffy, the sauce was well-balanced, and the vegetables were crisp and refreshing. Each element was executed so well, and it was a fun experience to assemble my own bao, playing with proportions and mixing different ingredients.  Would highly recommend to locals looking for a great meal, or tourists who might be checking out H Street or Union Market.
Innovative combo business model serving fusion flavors, but lacks proper cooking techniques
This place is incredible!
We got 4 dishes for takeout and all traveled really well. The lo mein was still pipping hot. Fantastic meal!
The food was delicious, but the manager is what makes this place amazing. Always ready to help, with quick quips for all the regulars, the man is a gem. Big recommendation for business travelers.

Not all restaurants are good at executing take out. Maketto consistently dominates. While some of their meals are labeled as small plates, they can feed up to three people. I’ve ordered two small plates and three meals and had enough for seven people. The price was about 70 bucks. It’s always hot and the vegetables are fresh. It’s the friendliness of the staff however that ties everything together.
Great staff great food!

This place is absolutely fantastic. Food is great, ambiance is perfect. The COVID operation is lovely. Makes me want to move closer to H St so I can come here more often. Great place to read a book with coffee or get brunch with friends.

Incredible food. We got the Gruyere Dumplings, which were absolutely phenomenal. I'd order these every single day. The Bao pork buns were very good, as was the spicy cauliflower. Drunken fried rice was very good, very large plate and a little on the spicy side. I found the spice a tad overwhelming, but my boyfriend thought it was perfect. The Maketto fried chicken was incredible and a HUGE portion. The breading is very thick, crispy, and flavorful. It came with thick slices of bread on the side. We ended up mixing the fried rice and the chicken , and it was even tastier. The Chinese opera cocktail was very  tasty, and the margarita was a standard margarita. All orders are placed through QR code at the table, so the only time we saw our server was when they brought food to the table. They were very friendly and quick. Everyone was masked and wearing gloves.
Very nice place, food is okay, great service, see you soon again.
Excellent authentic Taiwanese fare. The comic book and vinyl selection is well curated.

Honestly, one of the best meals of my life. We went for RW 2020 and it actually blew my mind. If everyone knew how to make the Wok Fried Snow Pea Tips from Maketto there would be world peace and 0% public health issues because everyone would happily be eating their vegetables and blissing out. I can't wait to go back.

Absolutely unreal. The flavors. The dishes. The cocktails. The service. Everything just feels so good. Such an enjoyable place. Can’t get over the food. It was so so good. Every dish. Mind blown. Thank you.
Wife and I have and will always love this spot. Fried Chicken is so good you might propose to your partner. (You’ve been warned)
My favorite place to go when I want to feel totally inadequate about my sense of style.  It's a lovely neighborhood joint offering a bit of everything, all of it interesting, most of it delicious.
Good place for coffee shop.
Yummy dim sum though the standout is the fried chicken. You will feel like you aren’t cool enough to enter just walk pass the t-shirts and millennial wares and enjoy the food.
The unlimited dumpling options is very unique and great.
The fried chicken here is excellent. Maketto also does coffee very well.
Trendy little shop offering a unique experience. Staff is top notch!

It was finally nice to see Maketto recognized by the Michelin Guide in 2020 (even if was only in the “Bib Gourmand” category. The reviewers nailed it when describing Maketto: it's the love child of the hip gods of fashion and food.  I first became familiar with Erik Bruner-Yang in 2012 when Toki Underground had exploded onto the scene. There was finally a spot that served DC’s void for quality ramen and it did it all while playing highly curated tunes in a chic, punk-inspired bungalow.  When Erik had just opened Maketto in 2015 with the help of Fundrise (a democratized real estate company) I was able to sit down with him to talk about the experience and about the future for Maketto.  Not only are you getting a top notch  interpretation of Cambodian and Taiwanese cooking, but Maketto is so much more.  It’s a 6,000 ft. communal marketplace that features high fashion, craft cocktails, some of DC’s best coffee, an events courtyard, and a roof deck. It’s not just a restaurant, it’s a living, breathing part of the community.  Erik and the team have always branded Maketto as “your home” and it truly is.  (P.S. - Last photo  of Jazz recs from superstar bartender Mr. Rob Stokes of October '71 - always a pleasure!)

Very small and cute place in the quite Jersey City neighborhood. It gets busy but the crowd is floating. They have very nice drinks and avocado toast. Crisp breads and warm teas make this a good study spot with great WiFi speed!
Please do their all-you-can-eat dumpling dinner. It’s still so relevant in a DC that is constantly evolving.
(Translated by Google) Somewhat spicy but very tasty food. Very friendly waiters  (Original) Comida algo picante pero muy sabrosa. Los meseros muy amables

Don't really understand why people rave about the food here.  Too much rice in the bowl, little meat. The veggies were watery and obviously packed in a humid container, leaving it all soggy. Pho had too much noodles and way overcooked making it all slimy and chewy. Was broth even used? Couldn't really taste it. Mushroom stuffed dumpling was extremely hot so open it up and let it sit a little.  The texture was unappetizingly mushy and didn't taste fresh.  The only good part was the fried dough that you dip in soy milk. But I guess anyone with a fryer, dough, and soy milk could make that.  I really liked the atmosphere though. Music can get loud but they play good songs. And the aura is very chill, open, and clean.
Great Cambodian food!!
Bone marrow laab was very, very good.

My mom and I visited Maketto on Sunday for Dim Sum. What a lovely experience it was! We had the crystal shrimp dumplings, potsticker dumplings and french toast. Everything was great and the portion sizes were plenty for us two to share those three small plates.

Great location, decor and outdoor space, nice menu and retail shop. I order a cappichino and was inpressed by the presentation and the smooth taste but I found hair in my water and on the coffee cup. When i brought it to the baristas attention he was not remorseful and looked frustrated. The manager at the bar was very friendly and helpful in getting me a refund and he also apologized for the mistake. The bar looks nice and the food looks good but I will not be returning.
Excellent
Very good coffee.
fantastic dim sum brunch - bring friends and an appetite

Great place to spend a couple of hours. We did the Dim Sum brunch and then migrated up to the cafe for a coffee. Also could have done some streewear shopping if we felt like it. Brunch was spicy and flavorful. Stick to the small plates and share with the table.
Very distinct and unique environment. Great place to go and hang out with friends.
Fun little coffee shop! Their 5 spice latte was very cool!
Never disappoints! The food is amazing and the ambience is very chic.

This is my new favorite spot on H street!  The staff was so kind and patient with us, my friends and I left that night talking about how much we look forward to coming back soon.  && the DC Brau collab tuk tuk is AMAZING.  highly recommend.

The environment is pretty modern, really cool.  The staff are well dressed and friendly.  The bartender Danny makes the best drinks (be creates his own as well). The "Jefe Azul" is great, perfect combo of salty and sweet. The food is great too. And the coffee. I just love it.

We've been going to Maketto since it opened. They have great service and food. It's usually pretty busy, so we like to sit at the bar (first come first serve). We love the pork buns and leek buns. Their cocktails are also fantastic! Last night I tried the fried chicken... OMG! So delicious.  Their lunch menu is pretty on point too and you can finish up at the coffee bar upstairs.

username: m i c h a e l

caption: Stop by this establishment in order to enjoy the DC restaurant week. They had a nice three-course meal for $35. I had the pork dumplings, crab fried rice with a poached egg and a caramel dessert that the name escapes me. although I did not have a reservation after a few minutes they were able to accommodate me.  The servers were nice gave very good suggestions and the establishment of super clean. they sell clothes shoes hats glasses books and I'm sure other commodities in the back that I did not get to see. It has a second-floor balcony a backdoor rooftop. From the outside looking in you would never guess this establishment with that big. the food was great the drinks were strong and overall I will be visiting again after restaurant week.

Maketto always has great food and cool vibes. My go-to bite when there is def the Bao Buns and I always enjoy checking out their merchandise, store, and the magazines they have on display there. Their pastries are always fresh and delicious and on any given day you'll hear your favorite song playing throughout the store. Its one of the best places to meetup with friends, find inspiration, and or work from a coffee shop. I recommend checking out their vending machine too there is always something cool inside of there.

The dim sum was great. The Sunday brunch menu is a selection from all their menus, so you don't need to order dim sum. However, the dim sum was my favorite. Both the shrimp dumplings and the vegetable gyoza melt in your mouth. The service was superb. Two different servers helped us. Food was brought out as it was ready. This was nice since it split it up into multiple courses, like traditional dim sum. I loved the vibe and the music. Will definitely keep it on my short list for brunch.
Good coffee, over priced but tasty small Asian fusion plates, all in an improbable shoe shop
Creative concept of a business consisting of cafe, restaurant, and retail shop! Food is good and beverages are great!
Pretty  good food.  Went with my family and ordered a few different things. Everything came out well.
The food is amazing! You can also shop a little while you wait to get seated.

Unique experience, sub par coffee bar. I got the Chai latte which was watery and had little flavor- which is surprising because I got it with oat milk which is flavorful in of itself! However, My husband got a  mocha which was much tastier. Even still, for these two twelve ounce drinks cost us 12 dollars.  Certainly not worth the money.
Trendy restraunt with delicious food ! Definitely try the spicy fried chicken

Really good food and not that expensive! The Bao is so good!!! Found this place by accident, kind of hidden, but it’s really cute, and the food portions are just at the right amount. I ordered Bao, and it came two big Bao buns. It was very filling. My husband ordered the Pho and it also looked and tasted amazing! I loved this place, and will be coming back with the rest of my family. 10/10 recommend and very pleased. :D
Love this place. Their combodian pho, Cold Noodle, their coffee and their service. Everything is great.
Interesting Asian Fusion food experience. Its a good blend of southeast Asia flavors. The cocktails are very good as well. They can get quite pricey if you want to be full.
Not sure what the hype is here. The xiaolongbao taste pretty good and the lamb noodles look really yummy
Great !

Is this a clothing store? Is this a restaurant? Is this a bar?  I'm still not sure what that classification should be. But I've enjoyed many things they offered.  Really great taste at pretty reasonable prices on the food. I recommend going on a weekend when their version of a dim sum service menu let's you choose from many offering.  Great food. Great service.

I went for a tasting collective event. The food service was as slow as pond water. What should have been a one hour event ran longer than 3. I quite frankly left before it finished. Will not be visiting this overhyped place again.
Awesome coffee/ streetwear / dim sum Only other place I've ever found egg tarts in the United States. Beautiful clean shop
Exciting drinks and always good food.  Best happy hour deal in town!  Be sure to check out their weekend dim sum; yum!
Great taste of home and excellent service!
The best Happy Hour I EVER had!! Every dish we ordered was out of this world, it was SO cheap and the guy behind the bar was wonderful! I will love there from now on!
Love the unlimited bao deal! Strongly suggest this place for groups.
Very good spring rolls and cocktails, awful chai (hot and iced) and so incredibly cold and loud. I'll be back when it's warmer. Until then, maybe not worth the journey.
Everything I've had on the food menu here has been delicious
Amazing dim sum place. Great service, great food, great atmosphere.
Food is awesome.

This place is ridiculously cool. When we first walked in, we thought it looked a little lame, but the people were so friendly that went back and have it a try. We got seated upstairs which was much cooler than downstairs. (They have this weird retail thing going on - don't let it throw you) THEN we found out about the absurdly good Happy Hour deal. for every drink you buy, wine beer or cocktail, you get a plate of dim sum for free, and the portions are big, and the food is excellent.we were all struck by how friendly and down-to-earth and seemingly happy the staff were. The happy hour deal is truly off the hook. You can basically get two drinks and enough food for a full dinner for free. Highly recommended.
Great food! Pork and chicken are fantastic!

The service is excellent and the food is absolutely brilliant! The concept behind this location is communal dining, so each dish is meant to be shared and are very generous in proportion. I shared the wok fried noodles, the dumplings, and the fried chicken with two others. They slightly staggered the arrival of the dishes so we could experience one at a time without having to wait for the food. The most amazing thing though is that each dish was better than the last. The dumplings (not traditional eastern dumplings) were crunchy on the outside and fantastically soft on the inside. The noodles were very smooth and savory, but definitely not too salty. Fried chicken was great as well, with a crunchy shell and tender chicken inside. Would definitely recommend this place.
Really great pour over experience

I can’t appreciate this restaurant enough. Their food is surprisingly very authentic! They are always crowded so I’ve been dining at the bar. Their bartenders are awesome! If you crave authentic chinese/southern-asian food, you’ll love this place!

oh my actual goodness  Maketto presented one of the best culinary experiences I've had in a long, long time. In a city overflowing with delicious dishes and innovative takes on Asian cuisine, Maketto goes above and beyond with its choice of ingredients and the way it constructs its dishes. There wasn't an item that I didn't like but if I had to make a single recommendation I'd say to go with the tofu app, rice noodles main, and thai tea ice cream for dessert. But everything is so wonderful that you'll want to go with a group and share and try everything. Plus it's SO vegetarian and gluten free friendly which isn't always offered for restaurants like this. The service is also fantastic (Ylli is the man!) and you can tell everyone working here is committed to a sense of community on H Street which makes being here cozy. I can't wait to come back.

Cute little coffee shop. Came here to do some work and be productive and will definitely do that again. =) Had a nice cuppuccino, some peace and some wifi. Its the small things. When its nice enough the outside setting is beautiful.

Maketto is a fantastic neighborhood spot, but really sets it apart is the commitment to be a part of the community. Last weekend we held a block party and on a whim reached out to Maketto to see if they would be interested in donating some food. Not only did they donate, they went above and beyond by providing us with an incredible spread. As our neighborhood continues to change and as new business come in, it is heartening to know that there are still folks who have interest in on just serving the community but being active participants in it. Bravo, Maketto, you have earned some customers for life!
THE BAO! My God I’m still dreaming about that Bao! Fried chicken is on point! But the lamb noodles are prepared to such a delight and with such flavor that nothing else really compares after.
Great food, not cheap
Buy expensive pants to go with your small plates, also maybe some art and a haircut. I don't think I'm joking
Maketto is a favorite. Awesome vibes all around. The perfect mix of cool and efficient. Nobody does it better.
Love it
Really nice experience, liked the baos and Cambodian cold noodle.
Good

When I come to DC, I make an effort to come to Maketto. The whole menu is delicious, but the fish is other-worldly and the eggplant is the ultimate comfort food. Staff have always been super friendly, knowledgeable, accommodating, and seem excited to talk about the food. The cocktails are also great.
One of the best things about the H St corridor.
Everything there is delicious.
Best almond crossiants in DC. Great place to study too.
Great experience, nice atmosphere,  seating inside and out.  Our bartender Adam, was very knowledgeable and social. Great menu. I will definitely return.
I’ve been here for restaurant week and to grab coffee and every time I’ve been in I’ve enjoyed the unique atmosphere and delicious food.

Great food and cocktails. They have happy hour specials at the bar which sounded worth trying, you get a dim sum with your drink. The bone marrow and spicy pork was delicious, as well as the Crystal shrimp dumplings. They were out of the lamp noodles which sucked but we will be back to try. Our waiter Dante was great and very knowledgable accommodating. Also the cheesecake dumpling was awesome, and I am not even a big cheesecake fan! Definitely worth stopping in.

This place has  been on my to list for sometime now. Upon my surprise I should have checked them out sooner. Everything was so great! The food was simply amazing. We had the shrimp dumplings, veggie dumplings ( which seem to be a spinach mix) and veggie spring rolls.  Rest assure I will be returning. Oh how could I Forget the drinks. The Margaritas are average prices but worth it!
Always great. Sad I don't come here more

It was my first time visiting this restaurant, and I had the Cambodian Pho, and it was...There are no words to describe how delicious the food is. My best friend had the wings, and her mom had fried rice.  If you get the chance, Maketto is a place that you should make it a point to visit.

Based on numerous positive online reviews, decided come here for lunch yesterday, ordered pork bao, shrimp dumpling, chicken lomein, and crispy tofu and basil. Oh my what a disaster lunch!  Shrimp dumplings (with tiny amount of shrimp) were *soaked* in fish sauce, the BBQ stuffing in the pork bao was way too *sweet*, chicken lomein dish was heavily seasoned and *soaked* in dark salty sauce, and the tofu in the crispy tofu dish is not crispy at all, and the dish itself was heavily seasoned and salty.  Easy paid parking, nice servers, okay atmosphere but the food was awful. This Maketto place is a pinnacle of online overhyped!
Good food, great service! My favorite was the peach sundae, it was amazing. <3
Had a fantastic quick snack and glass of wine. Bartender was friendly and the food and wine were delicious!
Soo good. I tried many things i hadn't had before . I don't even know what it was called . . The bun balls?  I thought it was awsome that they had a clothing store inside too

Cool little Asian cafe with great desserts and coffee! Unique setup with a clothing store, bar and cafe. Excellent flat white, very unique desserts, and flavorful but light Asian fare like Cambodian noodles and dumplings.
(Translated by Google) Neh.  (Original) Neh.

Another great H street find.  This place looks like a shoe store, but upstairs there's a lovely café  with great Asian dishes with a twist.  I loved the pickled veg that pops up often on H street.  The leek bao buns were excellent as was the spicy beef rice bowl.  The dessert I had was called cheesecake, but was this floral pastry role masterpiece.  I recommend this surprising lunch spot.
As a coffee shop this place is excellent, as a dim sum stop this misses the mark.
Very good and plentiful
Good coffee, music not too loud, clean, lots of natural light!
The food was amazing. I highly recommend the fried chicken- it pretty much changed my life. Great service, and our bartender Daniel was awesome.
Awesome food and great cafe.
Wonderful coffee and atmosphere to catch up with a friend!
Yum is the word!
Good place for the right price
Great Khmer fusion would recommend
Super chill (and kinda sexy) study spot.
We were a big group and ordered of most of the small and large plates, each had unique and delicious taste

Got lucky to catch HH at the cafe/bar on the 2nd floor and you get a choice of an app with every drink you order!  Worth a stop in, maybe not so much for the Xiao Long Bao dinner series but the regular menu items were pretty yumm! Hoping to try this chicken dish that pretty much every table was ordering one.
Egg tart 👌👌👌👌

Not sure what the Hype is all about for this place. The food were mediocre at best, service was there but could use improvement. I guess the expensive prices were fair because they need to make money for their store front. I'm just not use to dining in a place where people are just loitering and "hanging out" around your table.
Cute spot. Didn’t even realize the upper floor is a restaurant and a clothing store on the bottom. The pork baos and branzino are really good. The drinks are okay only if you get the right bartender.

Can here for dinner with a friend on a late Friday night. Wasn't too busy, though we still made a reservation to be safe.  Our server was prompt and super friendly- the whole place had a very chill and welcoming vibe.  We split some small plates, the pork buns and the fried cauliflower. Both were super delicious. Then we split one of their noodle dishes, it was so much food. Definitely enough for two people or left overs if no one want to share .  Delicious food, a bit on the pricey side, but so worth it!  If you're driving, parking is a bit hectic. There are metered spots up front, but then a few blocks off H st is 2hr neighborhood parking. If you park on H St, watch out for the trolley!
Cute and trendy spot! Good for working and chilling with friends.
A beautiful space on H Street with incredible food. Very unique place. Its got a great coffee bar open during the day as well.
Great coffee and baristas.  It should be noted that on Sundays the top bar does not serve cocktails (only the bottom bar does).

(Translated by Google) Excellent place to eat sushi and Japanese food, very tasty! Pleasant atmosphere and good attention.  (Original) Excelente lugar para comer sushi y comida japonesa, muy rico! Ambiente grato y buena atencion.

Delicious Cambodian/Taiwanese fusion in a comfortable and casual setting. All the food comes piping hot from the open kitchen and the mix of flavors is to die for. A bit out of the way on H Street NE, but definitely worth a trip!

I was told that this place had the best fried chicken boy were they wrong. The chicken was fried in corn meal it was not good at all to me. I only finished a quarter of it. They also gave us free apps during happy hour for ever drink order spring rolls, pork belly boa and 1 other item. We went with the egg rolls I didnt taste them but from the looks of them not good my guest only had a bite before se gave up.
Awesome food, great service, wished they were open longer on a Sunday
Food was very different.q
Went there to have lunch with a friend. Atmosphere is always dope and has great energy. Food is great and the location is wonderful.
very nice place for a quick bite and to relax
Everything is delicious. If you have let gone for breakfast yet or tried a ham and cheese or stake and cheese croissant yet. Make it a priority o do so now. No words.
Warm atmosphere, extremely friendly employees, great drinks, delicious food.

Went to this place for the first time a couple days ago and fell in LOVE. The overall layout & concept make for a great atmosphere. Went in for coffee and stayed for the gin. The bartender/barista Danny was very helpful. Definitely going to visit again
Absolutely delicious menu that changes weekly, the week I sent it had a southeast Asian cuisine which tasted delightful.
Blown away. Great food. Cool atmosphere. Top 5 places thus far in DC.
Super cool place - neat little store with awesome Asian food. Everything was really fresh and flavorful. They have a nice outdoor patio and it's very casual and low key.

Neat concept! the first floor is a shopping area with super cool items, a bar/restaurant and an outdoor area. The second floor has table to do work at and eat/drink. Its a coffee shop, boutique, restaurant, bar all in one!
Overpriced but cool atmosphere with good food.
Innovative and tasty dishes. Don't forget the desserts.

Wonderful experience yet. Best place we ate at this whole trip. Robs service on the second floor the music producer with the mustache and curly hair is the best. We loved the food and we loved the recommendations. This is the best place for a unique dining experience. Come check this place out. Everything we ate was good. The fried chicken is an acquired taste though.Maketto is a 6,000 sqft communal marketplace located in Washington DC, combining retail, restaurant, bar, and cafe experiences. The space features a modern/minimal attitude and includes a mix of 2 buildings, a courtyard, a roof deck, and a catwalk connecting the different spaces together. They said the following... "We wanted to create a space where everyone felt at home, whether it was to enjoy a coffee and a pastry, a nice dinner, a great selection of wines, to shop for new shoes, or to just work quietly in the cafe.  Our hope is that you learn/try something new and can always find a reason to come back to see us." -  Erik Bruner-Yang  &  Will Sharp

Maketto is one of my favorite local cafe concept shops to work, eat, and be inspired. The minimalist design and highly curated retail space is inviting. The food is stand out amongst the norm. Stop here to get the Lo Mein during lunch or …
Need to make a reservation for dinner. Food was fabulous
Exquisite atmosphere. Excellent cuisine paired with a stylish fashion shop. Definitely come if you can

Have never eaten in a restaurant-apparel store before but if all such experiences are like this one, will have to do so again soon! Service was terrific and portions were excellent for the price. Ordered from the prix-fixe menu and loved how they steamed the fish and the crystal shrimp dumplings. Also highly recommend the five spice fried chicken and bread.
Great food and service! The place must be great for having brunch during summer

As a morning cafe, 5⭐. Great americano & cold brew. Fresh pastries 🥐. Friendly service, comfy atmosphere. WiFi ✔️, but can be frustrating and weak. Only trick is finding the place (maybe a blessing; hidden gem).

I normally wouldn't eat in a fusion place, but Maketto surprised me with good quality of food. The pork bun was juicy with thin skin, can tell it was housemade. The lamb noodles was tasty with hand pulled noodles. Service was friendly, just the menu is small.

Really enjoy Maketto every time I come. Every dish is a slap in the face of flavor, in the best way. There are so many garlic and ginger-forward dishes with rich umami flavors as well. The strange flavor eggplant is amazing. I really like how clearly the idea behind the restaurant comes out through the flavors and presentation of the dishes. This is a great place for a date night or for a large group.

Part boutique, part East Asian/dim-sum place, 6/5 stars!  Excellent food for our Valentine's Day dinner and immensely helpful and personable service! We ordered several items from the standard dinner menu, including the fried chicken and the braised pork bao, and were not disappointed in the slightest. The portions are perfect for the price point and the cocktails were exactly what we'd hoped they'd be. There was a pre-fixe menu with a ton of options, but in the end I felt I wanted the braised lamb noodles stumbled into a dish unlike any I'd had before. We'll be back bringing friends and trying everything we didn't eat on the first go-round.
Hip spot that’s part coffee shop, part bar, and part clothing store. Stopped in for coffee and got a delicious oat latte and a matcha Rice Krispie treat!

I do however, love the overall vibe and layout of Maketto - it truly is an H street staple and one of the most unique restaurant experiences you can have in DC. This is a very unique restaurant in the district. The breakfast is great and the dinner is ever better. It has second floor balcony type seating it has a very nice patio. It has two bars. Excellent tea and coffee. They also sell Maketto merchandise, gear you can only get here so if you're into fashion this is also a cool place to visit. They host events here as well like art shows, photo shoots and concerts. This is one of my favorite restaurants in Washington D.C.!

Great coffee and a great variety of different Asian foods on offering. I had a pour over and the Spicy Beef Rice Bowl which was basically Bimbibap. The pour over was pretty great, and It was nice to see Maketto using Small Planes Coffee a local coffee roaster's coffee. The Spicy Beef Rice Bowl which was executed pretty good. The wife had the Steamed Pork Baozi, which she liked. While all of the food may not be exactly authentic, it is pretty close considering the blend of coffee shop/cafe and restaurant. All in all Maketto blends coffee shop and restaurant pretty well, and I'd definitely recommend this place if you are in the area and looking for something different to try!

Hip place to hang and eat. Modern/Chic/NYC street style. Instagrammable to say the least. Cafe upstairs with a variety of seating options. A couple of months ago we attempted to visit Maketto for Dim Sum on a Sunday morning but the wait was well over an hour and a half. I was skeptical that it was all hype because of the modern appearance and the on trend stuff being sold at the front of the space. However this past weekend we finally booked a reservation and experienced all the hype. All I can say, is that it was totally worth the wait.  First and foremost, all of the employees were so nice and friendly and helpful.  But on to the stuff you came here for - food. We got the veggie goyza, shrimp dumplings, strange flavored eggplant and blueberry and almond French toast. Everything was SO good. The veggie goyza was the perfect amount of spicy and crispy, as were the shrimp dumplings. The strange flavor eggplant was flavorful and everything on the plate went well together. My only suggestion would be a more flavorful French toast base. Everything on the plate was tasty, but the dread was dense and if you didn’t get enough cream or compote it wasnt as flavorful as everything else.

I really wasn't impressed. I stepped in on a Saturday afternoon for some coffee and a place to read for a little bit during a weekend stay in DC. Despite the the fact that the place was devoid of customers, I sat at the downstairs bar for at least five minutes while the multiple staffers behind it completely ignored me and socialized with each other. Eventually one of them deigned to recognize my existence and offered me a menu, only to tell me that I should probably go upstairs if I wanted coffee. Upstairs there were three customers and at least a dozen small tables, each of which had a "Reserved" sign on it. Finding this extremely odd, as they were not even remotely busy and there was a couple just sitting at one table casually studying, I asked if the tables actually were all reserved or if I could use one. A staffer with a rather chilly disposition told me that I could not; again, this place was DEAD and the staff was not busy, so besides them just not wanting to have to spend 10 seconds wiping it down when I finished my coffee I can't imagine why they wouldn't let me just sit at a damn table. Instead, I wound up sitting at the upstairs bar nursing a mediocre cold brew and attempting to read while the people behind the bar noisily chatted. Between the unwelcoming atmosphere, the somewhat rude staff, and the unremarkable coffee (Dunkin-level quality for Starbucks-level pricing), I'd recommend skipping this one.
